description:
## Scope

Retire `validate_specs_or_exit` (main.rs:47). Replace with two pure
analysis functions:

```rust
pub fn check_specs(prog: &Program, module: &Module) -> Vec<Diagnostic> {
    let mt = ir_typer::type_module(module);
    spec_check::validate_specs(prog, module, &mt)
}

pub fn check_patterns(prog: &Program, module: &Module) -> Vec<Diagnostic> {
    let mut reduced = module.clone();
    ir_reducer::reduce_module(&mut reduced);
    let reachable = ir_callgraph::reachable_fns(&reduced);
    let survivors: HashSet<(String, usize)> = reachable
        .iter()
        .filter_map(|fid| {
            let &idx = reduced.fn_idx.get(fid)?;
            let f = &reduced.fns[idx];
            let arity = f.block(f.entry).params.len();
            Some((f.name.clone(), arity))
        })
        .collect();
    pattern_check::check_program(prog, Some(&survivors))
}
```

Each is pure: takes inputs, returns diagnostics, no I/O, no exit.

## Driver migration

Each of the four driver sites (main.rs:243, 348, 656, 933) becomes:

```rust
let mut diags = check_specs(&prog, &module);
diags.extend(check_patterns(&prog, &module));
diag::report_or_exit(&diags, &sm);
```

Diagnostic ordering (spec errors before pattern warnings) is
preserved by `extend` order. Exit semantics preserved: any error
across either gate halts after both rendered.

## What gets removed

- The `validate_specs_or_exit` function and its callers.
- The fused-three-concerns shape at this gate. Analysis, presentation,
  and control flow each have their own home now.

## Testability dividend

`check_specs` and `check_patterns` become unit-testable without
process::exit shenanigans. Currently no unit tests exist for the
gate's analysis — only integration tests via fixtures. After this
ticket, gate-level unit tests become trivial. (Adding such tests is
optional follow-up, not required by acceptance.)

## Depends on

fz-0z4.3 (C — no second type_module to bundle) and fz-0z4.5 (E1 —
the sink it calls).

## Acceptance

- `cargo build` clean.
- All four driver paths (run, jit, dump, build/aot) produce
  byte-identical diagnostic output across the fixture matrix.
- `validate_specs_or_exit` no longer appears in the codebase.
- Exit behavior identical: any error halts; warnings print and
  continue.
